    {
      "title": "Starboy (Self Portrait)",
      "year": "December 2, 2019",
      "medium": "Watercolor and acrylic on wood",
      "dimensions": "58.5 x 30.5 in.",
      "description": "The painting that marked a turning point in artistic development and the beginning of a sustained inquiry into the cosmos, the Black body, and infinity. The infinite essence of the sun pierces rays into each spirit, regardless of experience on the physical plane, we are infinite, as infinite as the universe itself and the stardust running through our veins. Transforming the Black body into the cosmos: eternal, residing in a spiritual dimension. Within the visible spectrum exists racism, sexism, homophobia, transphobia, and discrimination. But in the UV spectrum, beyond the comprehension of the human eye, the Black body is a site of magic. Every Black person deserves to see themselves adorned by the stars.",
      "image": "/uploads/old/starboy.jpg"
    },
    {
      "title": "Entombment",
      "year": "June 20, 2019",
      "medium": "Watercolor on cardboard",
      "dimensions": "48 x 39 in.",
      "image": "/uploads/old/entombment.jpg",
      "description": "A narrative painting class project in which an existing work was chosen and recreated in the artist's own image. Drawing from Pontormo's Entombment of Christ (1525-28), the artist placed himself in the figure of Christ, with friends serving as models for the surrounding figures. A reinterpretation of a canonical work through personal identity and lived experience."
    },
